<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,356,597]" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,466,391,416]" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">
Condition of the 
<typeStatus box="[407,460,391,416]" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">type</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Genitalia dissected (
<figureCitation box="[708,792,391,416]" captionStart="FIGURES 49 – 54. 49" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1708,1730]" captionText="FIGURES 49 – 54. 49) Eurota [sic] hilaris (Syntype); 50) Gymnelia jordani (Lectotype); 51) Eurota [sic] marcia (Syntype); 52) Cosmosoma pseudothia (Syntype); 53) Eucyane variabilis roseofasciata (Lectotype); 54) Cosmosoma xanthomelan (Lectotype). Scale bars: 1 cm." pageId="11" pageNumber="516">
Fig. 
<number box="[763,792,391,416]" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" value="54.0">54</number>
</figureCitation>
) and kept in plastic vial pinned with the specimen. The dissection was made from the terminal portion of the abdomen, so most of the specimen is intact. The 
<typeStatus box="[1330,1378,429,453]" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">type</typeStatus>
is in otherwise good condition excepting that the tips of the forewings are slightly rubbed.
</paragraph>
